It would be nice to be able to have the Mail Archiver optionally _leave_ the mail on the mail server. Or, lacking that ability, it would be useful if Confluence did NOT automatically download mail from a mail server into the Confluence archive but only by command of the user with the warning that the mail would be permanently removed from the server.

Either way, folks could continue to use their regular mail applications and only use Confluence as the Archiver for the mail.

I would like to create a Quartz job which can be used to export a static version of the whole wiki automatically. Sort of like standard BackupJob but exporting HTML instead of XML. However, if one tries to invoke the getDescription() method of a space object retrieved using the Spring bean spaceManager (that's what the HTML exporter code will eventually do if you feed it with spaces retrieved using the spaceManager) in the Quartz thread, you'll get a HibernateException:

net.sf.hibernate.HibernateException: Could not initialize proxy - the owning Session was closed

Could this be fixed if it was possible to do something like this in the executeInternal() method of the job:

Session session = spaceManager.getSession(); // not implemented at the moment
Transaction tx = session.beginTransaction();
// do whatever with spaces, such as export a single space called "ds" to HTML...
Space space = spaceManager.getSpace("ds");
DefaultExportContext context = new DefaultExportContext(ImportExportManager.EXPORT_XML_TYPE_SPACE);
context.addWorkingEntity(space);
String exportPath = importExportManager.exportAs(ImportExportManager.TYPE_HTML, context);
session.flush();
session.clear();
tx.commit();

