Often we want to use the results of one macro as a parameter for another. This can be sometimes accomplished if the results are communicated between macros through the body, but many times the information must be passed to a parameter. For example, I'd like to be able to do things like this:

{include:{i:pageTitle} FAQ}

Where {i} is a macro that returns basic page information, in this case the current page title.  The macro above would, on a page titles "Confluence", include the a page called "Confluence FAQ".

If you try and link to an attachment on a blog post, it reports that the resource can't be found. Given that the "insert image" box in thw WYSIWYG editor can't search for images in other pages (or posts), it'd be nice to be able to link (and embed) images from blog posts into other posts or pages.

For instance, the following syntax doesn't work (excluding the noformat tags, if they show up):

{noformat}
!/2006/10/01/Blog Post^attachment.png!
{noformat}

