If you are in editing mode, you should be able to see visually if the buffer has been modified or not.  For example, on the Mac, there is a convention that if there is a black dot in the close button for the window, then the document in that window has been modified and therefore must either be saved or discarded.

This feature is even more important in a wiki because there is no way (currently) the browser can know that you should be asked to save or discard before you either close the window or replace its contents with something else.

At least a glaring visual indication, like perhaps a red border around the edit area or something, would help with the ubiquitous accidental abandonment problem.

