I have 3GB of audio files.  There is no way I want to crud up my mysql database with additional copies of these.

There should be a way to attach a file to a page by reference, using its path in the htdocs folder, so that when it is used it is read from the file rather than from the database.

In particular, I want to be able to embed an aac (a.k.a. MPEG4 Audio) file directly from the file in the file system, and I see I can't do that.

